I need to identify the amount of profit after all expenses have been deducted from revenue, which is the "Net Profit" line item, and extract 5 component sub-items that contribute to this calculation.

Step 1: Looking at the income statement, I can see that the "Net Profit" is 143922.03.

Step 2: Now I need to identify 5 key sub-items that contribute to this calculation:
- The "Total Revenue" is 851679.79
- The "Cost of Goods Sold" is 543370.00
- The "Total Expenses" is 129579.16
- The "Interest Income" is 7775.44
- The "Tax Expense" is 42584.04

This makes sense because:
Net Profit = Total Revenue - Cost of Goods Sold - Total Expenses + Interest Income - Tax Expense
= 851679.79 - 543370.00 - 129579.16 + 7775.44 - 42584.04 = 143922.03
